/**
 * The food artwork, embedded as a single WebP sprite sheet.
 *
 * This is the artist's original illustration, processed once offline and baked
 * in — not drawn by code. The processing did four things: cut the white
 * background away with a flood fill from the edges (a plain "delete near-white"
 * would have punched holes in the candy's white stripes and the cake's cream
 * top, which are near-white but ENCLOSED), punched out the donut's hole,
 * recoloured the donut frosting to baby blue and the cupcake frosting to green
 * by rotating hue only where it fell in the pink band (335-15 degrees, which
 * does not overlap the tan dough at 20-40), and packed the eight foods into a
 * 4x2 grid, each centred in its cell and scaled so its largest dimension fills
 * the cell.
 *
 * WebP rather than PNG because it is 7x smaller here: the same sheet is 1056KB
 * as a PNG data URI and 143KB as WebP at quality 0.95, and the artwork is flat
 * vector shading where that quality loss is invisible. BootScene falls back to
 * the drawn art in data/foodArt if the sheet ever fails to decode.
 *
 * Cell order is the merge chain, tier 1 to 8:
 *   candy, macaron, cookie, donut / cinnamon roll, cream puff, cupcake, cake
 */

/** Pixel size of one cell in the sheet. */
export const SHEET_CELL = 288;
/** Grid layout of the sheet. */
export const SHEET_COLS = 4;
export const SHEET_ROWS = 2;

export const FOOD_SHEET =
  "data:image/webp;base64,";
